soc.message

Interface SOCMessageFromUnauthClient

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SOCAuthRequest, SOCCreateAccount, SOCDisconnect, SOCGameOptionGetDefaults, SOCGameOptionGetInfos, SOCImARobot, SOCJoinChannel, SOCJoinGame, SOCLeaveAll, SOCLocalizedStrings, SOCNewGameWithOptionsRequest, SOCScenarioInfo, SOCVersion

    public interface SOCMessageFromUnauthClient
    This marker is for any SOCMessage type which an unauthenticated client can send. (The type might also be sent by a client which has already authenticated.)

    Other message types may be rejected by server if the client hasn't yet authenticated. Instead of processing the message, server will reply with SOCStatusMessage(SV_MUST_AUTH_FIRST).

    Since:
    2.4.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin <jeremy@nand.net>
